obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (35888)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35888&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Inchek Tyres Limited and`
  line `National Rubber Manufacturers Limited (Nationalisation) Act, 1984.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 14th day of February, 1984.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (35889)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35889&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the 14th day of February 1984;`
  line
  line `(b) "Commissioner" means the Commissioner of Payments appointed under section 15;`
  line
  line `(c) "existing Government company" means a Government company which is carrying on`
  line `business on the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(d) "new Government company" means a Government company formed and registered on or after`
  line `the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(e) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "specified date", in relation to any provision of this Act, means such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify for the purposes of that provision, and different dates may`
  line `be specified for different provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "two companies" means the Inchek Tyres Limited and the National Rubber Manufacturers`
  line `Limited, being companies as defined in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), and having their`
  line `registered offices at "Leslie House", 19 Jawaharlal Nehru Road, Calcutta-700013;`
  line
  line `(i) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (35890)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government of the undertakings of the two companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35890&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On the appointed day, the undertakings of each of the two companies, and the right, title`
  line `and interest of each of the two companies in relation to its undertakings, shall, by virtue of the Act, stand`
  line `transferred to, and shall vest in, the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (35891)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `General effect of vesting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35891&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The undertakings of each of the two companies referred to in`
  line `section 3 shall be deemed to include all assets, rights, lease-holds, powers, authorities and privileges, and`
  line `all property, movable and immovable, including lands, buildings, workshops, stores, instruments,`
  line `machinery and equipment, cash balances, cash on hand, cheques, demand drafts, reserve funds,`
  line `investments, book debts and all other rights and interest in, or arising out of such, property as were`
  line `immediately before the appointed day in the ownership, possession, power or control of such company`
  line `whether within or outside India, and all books of account, registers and all other documents of whatever`
  line `nature relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) All properties as aforesaid which have vested in the Central Government under section 3 shall, by`
  line `force of such vesting, be freed and discharged from any trust, obligation, mortgage, charge, lien and all`
  line `other incumbrances affecting them, and any attachment, injunction, decree or order of any court, tribunal`
  line `or other authority restricting the use of such properties in any manner or appointing any receiver in`
  line `respect of the whole or any part of such properties shall be deemed to have been withdrawn.`
  line
  line `(3) Every mortgagee of any property which has vested under this Act in the Central Government and`
  line `every person holding any charge, lien or other interest in, or in relation to, any such property shall give,`
  line `within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, an intimation to the Commissioner of such`
  line `mortgage, charge, lien or other interest.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the mortgagee of any property referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) or any other person holding any charge, lien or other interest in, or in relation to , any such`
  line `property shall be entitled to claim, in accordance with his rights and interest, payment of the mortgage`
  line `money or other dues, in whole or in part, out of the amount specified, in relation to the company owning`
  line `such property, in the First Schedule, and also out of the amounts referred to in section 9, but, no such`
  line `mortgage, charge, lien or other interest shall be enforceable against any property which has vested in the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Any licence or other instrument granted to either of the two companies in relation to any`
  line `undertaking which has vested in the Central Government under section 3 at any time before the appointed`
  line `day and in force immediately before that day shall continue to be in force on and after such day in`
  line `accordance with its tenor in relation to an for the purposes of such undertaking, and , on and from the date`
  line `of vesting of such undertaking under section 6 in an existing Government company, or under section 7 in`
  line `a new Government company, the existing, or new, Government company, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `deemed to be substituted in such licence or other instrument as if such licence or other instrument had`
  line `been granted to such existing, or new, Government company and such existing, or new, Government`
  line `company, shall hold it for the remainder of the period for which the company to which it was granted`
  line `would have held it under the terms thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) If, on the appointed day, any, suit, appeal or other proceeding of whatever nature, in relation to`
  line `any property which has vested in the Central Government under section 3, instituted or preferred by or`
  line `against either of the two companies is pending, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be, in any`
  line `way, prejudicially affected by reason of the transfer of the undertakings of such company or of anything`
  line `contained in this Act, but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be continued, prosecuted or enforced`
  line
  line `by or against the Central Government, or where the undertakings of the two companies vest under`
  line `section 6 or section 7 in an existing, or a new, Government company, by or against such Government`
  line company.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (35892)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Companies to be liable for certain prior liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35892&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every liability, other than the liability`
  line `specified in sub-section (2), of each of the two companies in respect of any period prior to the appointed`
  line `day, shall be the liability of the concerned company and shall be enforceable against it and not against the`
  line `Central Government, or where the undertakings of the two companies vest in an existing, or a new,`
  line `Government Company, against such Government company.`
  line
  line `(2) Any liability arising in respect of materials supplied to either of the two companies after the`
  line `management of its undertakings had been taken over by the Central Government, shall, on and from the`
  line `appointed day, be the liability of the Central Government or of the existing, or new, Government`
  line `company aforesaid, and shall be discharged by that Government or, as the case may be, the existing, or`
  line `new, Government company, as and when repayment for such supplies becomes due and payable.`
  line
  line `(3) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that--`
  line
  line `(a) save as otherwise expressly provided in this section or in any other provision of this Act, no`
  line `liability, other than the liability specified in sub-section (2), of either of the two companies in relation`
  line `to its undertakings in respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be enforceable against the`
  line `Central Government, or, where the undertakings of the two companies vest in an existing, or a new,`
  line `Government company, against such Government company;`
  line
  line `(b) no award, decree or order of any court, tribunal or other authority in relation to the`
  line `undertakings of either of the two companies, passed on or after the appointed day, in respect of any`
  line `matter, claim or dispute, not being a matter, claim or dispute in relation to any matter referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2), which arose before that day, shall be enforceable against the Central Government, or`
  line `where the undertakings of the two companies vest in an existing, or a new, Government company,`
  line `against such Government company;`
  line
  line `(c) no liability incurred by either of the two companies before the appointed day, for the`
  line `contravention of any provision of law for the time being in force, shall be enforceable against the,`
  line `Central Government, or, where the undertakings of the two companies vest in an existing, or a new,`
  line `Government company, against such Government company.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (35921)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power of Central Government to direct vesting of the undertakings of the two companies in an existing Government Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35921&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 3 and 4, and`
  line `subject to the provisions of section 7, the Central Government may, if it is satisfied that an existing`
  line `Government company is willing to comply, or has complied with such terms and conditions as that`
  line `Government may think fit to impose, direct, by notification, that the undertakings of each of the two`
  line `companies and the right, title and interest of each of the two companies in relation to its undertakings`
  line `which have vested in the Central Government under section 3, shall, instead of continuing to vest in the`
  line `Central Government, vest in that existing Government company either on the date of the notification or`
  line `on such earlier or later date (not being a date earlier than the appointed day) as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(2) Where the right, title and interest of the two companies, in relation to their undertakings vest,`
  line `under sub-section (1), in an existing Government company, that Government company shall, on and from`
  line `the date of such vesting, be deemed to have become, and, until the transfer of the undertakings, by virtue`
  line `of the provisions of section 7, to a new Government company, be deemed to be, the owner in relation to`
  line `such undertakings, and the rights and liabilities of the Central Government in relation to such`
  line `undertakings shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to have become, and, until the date of`
  line `such transfer, be deemed to be, the rights and liabilities, respectively, of that existing Government`
  line company.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (35922)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Transfer of the undertakings of the two companies from an existing Government company to a new Government company`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35922&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 3 and 4, where the`
  line `undertakings of each of the two companies have been directed, under sub-section (1) of section 6, to vest`
  line
  line `in an existing Government company, the Central Government may, if it is satisfied that a new`
  line `Government company is willing to comply, or has complied, with such terms and conditions as that`
  line `Government may think fit to impose, declare, by notification, that the undertakings of each of the two`
  line `companies and the right, title and interest of each of the two companies in relation to its undertakings be`
  line `transferred to that new Government company, and on the issue of such declaration, the right, title and`
  line `interest of each of the two companies in relation to its undertakings which had been directed under subsection (1) of section 6 vest in an existing Government company, shall, instead of continuing to vest in`
  line `that existing Government Company, vest in that new Government company with effect from the date on`
  line `which such declaration is made.`
  line `(2) Where the right, title and interest of the existing Government company in relation to the`
  line `undertakings of the two companies vest, under sub-section (1), in a new Government company, that`
  line `Government company shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to have become the owner`
  line `in relation to such undertakings and the rights and liabilities of the existing Government company in`
  line `relation to such undertakings, shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to have become the`
  line `rights and liabilities, respectively, of that new Government company`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (35895)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Payment of amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35895&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `For the transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government, under`
  line `section 3, of the undertakings of each of the two companies, and the right, title and interest of each of the`
  line `two companies in relation to its undertakings, there shall be paid by the Central Government to each of`
  line `the two companies, in cash and in the manner specified in Chapter VI, amount equal to the amount`
  line `specified against the name of such company in the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (35896)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Payment of further amounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35896&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the deprivation of the two companies of the management`
  line `of their undertakings during the period commencing on the date on which the undertakings of each such`
  line `company was taken over in pursuance of the orders made by the Central Government under the provisions`
  line `of the Industries (Development and Regulation) Act, 1951 (65 of 1951) and ending on the appointed day,`
  line `there shall be paid by the Central Government to each of the Companies in cash, an amount of rupees fifty`
  line thousand.
  line
  line `(2) The amount referred to in section 8 and the amount specified in sub-section (1) shall carry simple`
  line `interest at the rate of four per cent. per annum for the period commencing on the appointed day and`
  line `ending on the date on which payment of such amounts is made by the Central Government to the`
  line Commissioner.
  line
  line `(3) The amount referred to in sub-section (1) and the amount determined in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2) shall be given by the Central Government to the two companies in addition`
  line `to the amount specified in section 8.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the liabilities of either of the two companies`
  line `in relation to its undertakings which have vested in the Central Government under section 3, shall be`
  line `discharged from the amount referred to in section 8, and also from the amount specified in sub-section (1)`
  line `and the amount determined under sub-section (2), in accordance with the rights and interests of the`
  line `creditors of the two companies.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (35897)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Management, etc., of the undertakings of the two companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35897&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The general superintendence,`
  line `direction, control and management of the affairs and business of the undertakings of each of the two`
  line `companies, the right, title and interest in relation to which have vested in the Central Government under`
  line `section 3, shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) where a direction has been given by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6, vest on and from the date specified in such direction, in the existing Government company`
  line `specified therein; or`
  line
  line `(b) where a declaration has been made under sub-section (1) of section 7, vest, on and from the`
  line `date of such declaration, in the new Government company specified therein;`
  line
  line `and thereupon the existing, or new, Government company so specified, shall be entitled to exercise, to the`
  line `exclusion of all other persons, all such powers and do all such things as either, or both, of the two`
  line `companies, is or are, authorised to exercise and do in relation to its or their undertakings.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (35923)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Duty of persons in charge of management of undertakings of the two companies to deliver all assets, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35923&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the vesting of the management of the undertakings of the two companies in an`
  line `existing, or a new, Government company, all persons in charge of the management of the undertakings of`
  line `either of the two companies immediately before such vesting shall be bound to deliver to such`
  line `Government company, all assets, books of account, registers and other documents in their custody`
  line `relating to the undertakings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may issue such directions as it may deem desirable in the circumstances`
  line `of the case to the existing, or new, Government company and such Government company may also, if it is`
  line `considered necessary so to do, apply to the Central Government at any time for instructions as to the`
  line `manner in which the management of the undertakings of the two companies shall be conducted or in`
  line `relation to any other matter arising in the course of such management.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (35899)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Duty of persons to account for assets, etc., in their possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35899&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who has, on`
  line `the appointed day, in his possession or under his control any assets, books, documents or other papers`
  line `relating to the undertakings owned by either of the two companies, which have vested in the Central`
  line `Government or in an existing, or a new, Government company under this Act, shall be liable to account`
  line `for the said assets, books, documents and other papers to the Central Government or the existing, or new,`
  line `Government company, as the case may be, and shall deliver them to the Central Government or the`
  line `existing, or new, Government company or to such person or persons as the Central Government or the`
  line `existing, or new, Government company may specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or the Government company aforesaid may take, or cause to be taken, all`
  line `necessary steps for securing possession of the undertakings of the two companies which have vested in`
  line `the Central Government or the Government company under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The two companies shall, within such period as the Central Government may allow in this behalf,`
  line `furnish to that Government a complete inventory of all their properties and assets, as on the appointed`
  line `day, pertaining to the undertakings which have vested in the Central Government under section 3, and, for`
  line `this purpose, the Central Government or the Government company aforesaid shall afford to the two`
  line `companies all reasonable facilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (35900)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Continuance of employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35900&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who has been, immediately before the appointed`
  line `day, employed in any undertaking of either of the two companies shall become,--`
  line
  line `(a) on and from the appointed day, an employee of the Central Government, and`
  line
  line `(b) where the undertakings of the two companies are directed, under section 6 or under section 7,`
  line `to vest, in an existing, or a new, Government company, an employee of such Government company`
  line `on and from the date of such vesting,`
  line
  line `and shall hold office or service under the Central Government or the existing, or new, Government`
  line `company, as the case may be, with the rights and privileges as to pension, gratuity and other matters,`
  line `admissible to him immediately before the appointed day, as modified by the Memorandum of Settlement`
  line `signed by the representatives of the management and the employees of each of the two companies on the`
  line `10th day of February, 1984, and shall continue to do so unless and until his employment under the Central`
  line `Government or the existing, or new, Government company, as the case may be, is duly terminated or until`
  line `his remuneration and other conditions of service are duly altered by the Central Government, or the`
  line `existing, or new, Government company, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other person employed`
  line `in any undertaking of either of the two companies, to the Central Government or the existing, or new,`
  line `Government company, shall not entitle such officer or other employee to any compensation under this Act`
  line `or any other law for the time being in force and no such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal`
  line `or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (35901)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Provident fund and other funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35901&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where either of the two companies has established a`
  line `provident fund, superannuation, welfare or other fund for the benefit of the persons employed in any of its`
  line `undertakings, the moneys relatable to the officers or other employees whose services have become`
  line `transferred by or under this Act to the Central Government or an existing, or a new, Government`
  line `company shall, out of the moneys standing, on the appointed day, to the credit of such provident fund,`
  line `superannuation, welfare or other fund, stand transferred to, and shall vest in, the Central Government or`
  line `the existing, or new, Government company, as the care may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The moneys which stand transferred under sub-section (1) to the Central Government or the`
  line `existing, or new, Government company, as the case may be, shall be dealt with by that Government or the`
  line `existing, or new, Government company in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (35902)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Appointment of Commissioner of Payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35902&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, for the`
  line `purpose of disbursing the amounts payable under sections 8 and 9 to each of the two companies, by`
  line `notification, appoint a Commissioner of Payments.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint such other persons as it may think fit to assist the`
  line `Commissioner and thereupon the Commissioner may authorise one or more of such persons also to`
  line `exercise all or any of the powers exercisable by him under this Act and different persons may be`
  line `authorised to exercise different powers.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person authorised by the Commissioner to exercise any of the powers exercisable by the`
  line `Commissioner may exercise those powers in the same manner and with the same effect as if they have`
  line `been conferred on that person directly by this Act and not by way of authorisation.`
  line
  line `(4) The salaries and allowances of the Commissioner and other persons appointed under this section`
  line `shall be defrayed out of the Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (35903)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Payment by Central Government to the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35903&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall,`
  line `within thirty days from the specified date, pay in cash to the Commissioner, for payment to each of the`
  line `two companies,--`
  line
  line `(a) an amount equal to the amount specified against the name of such company in the First`
  line `Schedule; and`
  line
  line `(b) an amount equal to the amounts payable to each of the two company in the First schedule; and`
  line
  line `(2) A deposit account shall be opened by the Central Government in favour of the Commissioner in`
  line `the Public Account of India and every amount paid under this Act to the Commissioner shall be deposited`
  line `by him to the credit of the said deposit account and the said deposit account shall be operated by the`
  line Commissioner.
  line
  line `(3) Separate records shall be maintained by the Commissioner in respect of the undertakings of each`
  line `of the two companies in relation to which payments have been made to him under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Interest accruing on the amount standing to the credit of the deposit account referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) shall enure to the benefit of the two companies`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (35904)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Certain powers of Central Government or existing, or new, Government company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35904&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government or the existing, or new, Government company, as the case may be, shall be entitled`
  line `to receive up to the specified date, to the exclusion of all other persons, any money due to either of the`
  line `two companies in relation to its undertakings which have vested in the Central Government or the`
  line
  line `existing, or new, Government company, as the case may be, and realised after the appointed day`
  line `notwithstanding that the realisation pertains to a period prior to the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government, or the existing, or new, Government company, as the case may be, may`
  line `make a claim to the Commissioner with regard to every payment made by it after the appointed day, for`
  line `discharging any liability of either of the two companies, not being any liability specified in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 5, in relation to any period prior to the appointed day, and every such claim`
  line `shall have priority, in accordance with the priorities attaching, under this Act, to the matter in relation to`
  line `which such liability has been discharged by the Central Government or the existing, or new, Government`
  line company.
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the liabilities of either of the two companies in respect of`
  line `any transaction prior to the appointed day which have not been discharged on or before the specified date`
  line `shall be the liabilities of the respective company`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (35905)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Claims to be made to the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35905&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every person having a claim against either of the`
  line `two companies with regard to any of the matters specified in the Second Schedule pertaining to any`
  line `undertakings owned by it, shall prefer such claim before the Commissioner within thirty days from the`
  line `specified date:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Commissioner is satisfied that the claimant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from preferring the claim within the said period of thirty days, be may entertain the claim within a further`
  line `period of thirty days but not thereafter.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (35906)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Priority of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35906&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The claims arising out of the matters specified in the Second Schedule shall`
  line `have priorities in accordance with the following principles, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Category I shall have precedence over all other categories and Category II shall have`
  line `precedence over Category III, and so on;`
  line
  line `(b) the claims specified in each of the categories shall rank equally and be paid in full, but, if the`
  line `amount is insufficient to meet such claims in full, they shall abate in equal proportions and be paid`
  line `accordingly; and`
  line
  line `(c) the question of discharging any liability with regard to a matter specified in a lower category`
  line `shall arise only if a surplus is left after meeting all the liabilities specified in the immediately higher`
  line category.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (35907)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Examination of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35907&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of the claims made under section 18, the Commissioner`
  line `shall arrange the claims in the order of priorities specified in the Second Schedule and examine the same`
  line `in accordance with such order.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on examination of the claims, the Commissioner is of opinion that the amount paid to him`
  line `under this Act is not sufficient to meet the liabilities specified in any lower category, he shall not be`
  line `required to examine the claims in respect of such lower category.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (35908)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Admission or rejection of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35908&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) After examining the claims with reference to the`
  line `priorities specified in the Second Schedule, the Commissioner shall fix a date on or before which every`
  line `claimant shall file the proof of his claim.`
  line
  line `(2) Not less than fourteen days' notice of the date so fixed shall be given by advertisement in one`
  line `issue of any daily newspaper in the English language having circulation in the major part of the country`
  line `and in one issue of any daily newspaper in such regional language as the Commissioner may consider`
  line `suitable, and every such notice shall call upon the claimant to file the proof of his claim with the`
  line `Commissioner within the period specified in the advertisement.`
  line
  line `(3) Every claimant who fails to file the proof of his claim within the period specified by the`
  line `Commissioner shall be excluded from the disbursement made by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner shall, after such investigation as may, in his opinion, be necessary and after`
  line `giving the concerned company an opportunity of refuting the claim and after giving the claimant a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard, admit or reject by order in writing the claim in whole or in part.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commissioner shall have the power to regulate his own procedure in all matters arising out of`
  line `the discharge of his functions, including the place or places at which he may hold his sittings and shall,`
  line `for the purpose of making any investigation under this Act, have the same powers as are vested in a civil`
  line `court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the summoning and enforcing the attendance of any witness and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) the discovery and production of any document or other material object producible as`
  line evidence;
  line
  line `(c) the reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) the issuing of any commission for the examination of witnesses.`
  line
  line `(6) Any investigation before the Commissioner shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Commissioner shall be`
  line `deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(7) A claimant who is dissatisfied with the decision of the Commissioner may prefer an appeal`
  line `against such decision to the principal civil court of original jurisdiction within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction the registered office of the concerned company is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a person who is a Judge of a High Court is appointed, to be the Commissioner`
  line `such appeal shall lie to the High Court exercising jurisdiction over the place in which the registered office`
  line `of the concerned company is situated and such appeal shall be heard and disposed of by not less than two`
  line `Judges of that High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (35909)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Disbursement of money by Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35909&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `After admitting a claim under this Act, the amount`
  line `due in respect of such claim shall be paid by the Commissioner to the person or persons to whom such`
  line `amount is due, and on such payment, the liability of each of the two companies in respect of such claim`
  line `shall stand discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (35910)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Disbursement of amounts to the companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35910&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, out of the moneys paid to him in relation`
  line `to the undertakings of either of the two companies, there is a balance left after meeting the liabilities as`
  line `specified in the Second Schedule, the Commissioner shall disburse such balance to the concerned`
  line company.
  line
  line `(2) Where the possession of any machinery, equipment or other property has vested in the Central`
  line `Government or the existing, or new, Government company under this Act, but such machinery,`
  line `equipment or other property does not belong to either of the two companies, it shall be lawful for the`
  line `Central Government or the existing, or new, Government company, as the case may be, to continue to`
  line `possess such machinery or equipment or other property on the same terms and conditions under which`
  line `they were possessed by either of the two companies immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (35911)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Undisbursed or unclaimed amount to be deposited with the general revenue account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35911&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `money paid to the Commissioner which remains undisbursed or unclaimed on the date immediately`
  line `preceding the date on which the office of the Commissioner is finally wound up, shall be, transferred by`
  line `the Commissioner, before his office is finally wound up, to the general revenue account of the Central`
  line `Government; but a claim to any money so transferred may he preferred to the Central Government by the`
  line `person entitled to such payment and shall be dealt with as if such transfer had not been made, and the`
  line `order, if any, for the payment of the claim being treated as an order for the refund of revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (35912)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Act to have over-riding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35912&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law, other than this Act, or in any decree or order of any court, tribunal or`
  line `other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (35924)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Contracts to cease to have effect unless ratified by the Central Government or existing, or New, Government company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35924&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every contract entered into by either of the two companies in relation to`
  line `any of its undertakings which has vested in the Central Government under section 3 for any service, sale`
  line `or supply, and in force immediately before the appointed, day, shall, on and from the expiry of a period of`
  line `one hundred and eighty days from such day, cease to have effect unless such contract is, before the expiry`
  line `of that period, ratified, in writing, by the Central Government or the existing, or new, Government`
  line `company and in ratifying such contract, the Central Government or the existing, or new, Government`
  line `company may make such alteration or modification therein as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government or the existing, or new, Government company shall not omit to`
  line `ratify a contract and shall not make any alteration or modification in a contract--`
  line
  line `(a) unless it is satisfied that such contract is unduly onerous, or has been entered into in bad faith,`
  line `or is detrimental to the interests of the Central Government or such Government company; and`
  line
  line `(b) except after giving the parties to the contract a reasonable opportunity of being heard and`
  line `except after recording in writing its reasons for refusal to ratify the contract or for making any`
  line `alteration or modification therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (35914)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35914&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) having in his possession, custody or control any property forming part of any undertaking of`
  line `either of the two companies, wrongfully withholds such property from the Central Government or the`
  line `existing, or new, Government company; or`
  line
  line `(b) wrongfully obtains possession of, or retains, any property forming part of any undertaking of`
  line `either of the two companies; or`
  line
  line `(c) wilfully withholds or fails to furnish to the Central Government or the existing, or new,`
  line `Government company or any person or body of persons specified by that Government or Government`
  line `company, any document relating to such undertaking, which may be in his possession, custody or`
  line `control; or`
  line
  line `(d) fails to deliver to the Central Government or the existing, or new, Government company, as`
  line `the case may be, or any person or body of persons specified by that Government, or Government`
  line `company, any assets, books of account, registers or other documents in his possession, custody or`
  line `control, relating to the undertakings of either of the two companies; or`
  line
  line `(e) wrongfully removes or destroys any property forming part of any undertaking of either of the`
  line `two companies or prefers any claim which he knows or has reasonable cause to believe to be false or`
  line `grossly inaccurate,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (35915)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35915&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (35916)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35916&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or the existing, or new, Government company or any officer or`
  line `other employee of that Government or the Government company or any person authorised by that`
  line `Government or Government company for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit, or other legal proceeding, shall lie against the Central Government or the existing, or`
  line `new, Government company, or any officer or other employee of that Government or Government`
  line `company or any person authorised by that Government or Government company for any damage caused`
  line `or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (35917)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35917&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, direct that all or any`
  line `of the powers exercisable by it under this Act, other than the powers conferred by this section, section 31`
  line `or section 32, may also be exercised by such person or persons as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any delegation of power is made under sub-section (1), the person to whom such power`
  line `has been delegated shall act under the direction, control and supervision of the Central Government`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (35918)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35918&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the time within which, and the manner in which, an intimation referred to in sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 4 shall be given;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which the moneys in any provident fund or other fund referred to in section 14`
  line `shall be dealt with;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (35919)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35919&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act the Central Government may by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the appointed`
  line day.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (35920)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572&sectionId=35920&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00004_198417_1517807326572
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Inchek Tyres Limited and National Rubber Manufacturers Limited`
  line `(Nationalisation) Ordinance, 1984 (4 of 1984), is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
